Polish Stocks: Grupa Lotos, NWR, Pekao, PKO Bank, Pragma Trade

-- B y   P a w e l   K o z l o w s k i
-- 
2011-06-06T16:07:38Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-06/polish-stocks-lotos-nwr-pekao-pko-pragma-trade-zachodni.html
Poland ’s WIG20 Index fell 14.84, or
0.5 percent, to 2,868.98 in Warsaw, decreasing for a fourth day.  The following are among the most active stocks on the
 Warsaw Stock Exchange  today. Stock symbols follow company names.  Grupa Lotos SA (LTS)  , Poland’s second-largest refiner,
slipped 0.4 zloty, or 0.9 percent, to 46.1 zloty, the lowest
level in more than a week. Oil dropped on signs of a slowdown in
demand as OPEC ministers arrived in Vienna to discuss production
quotas.  New World Resources NV (NWR)  , the largest Czech coking-
coal producer, increased 0.5 zloty, or 1.3 percent, to 40 zloty
in Warsaw trading, rising for the first time in five days. Its
14-day relative strength index, which shows how rapidly prices
advanced or dropped during a specified time period, was at 23.5
on June 3. A reading of 30 or below signals to some investors
that shares are set to rise.  PKO Bank Polski SA (PKO PW), Poland’s biggest bank,
retreated for a third day, losing 0.48 zloty, or 1.1 percent, to
43.32 zloty as Deutsche Bank AG removed the stock from its “top
pick” list, citing the share price’s gain this year.  Pragma Trade SA (PTRA PW) sank 0.4 zloty, or 13 percent, to
2.8 zloty as the Polish cling-film producer started trading on
Warsaw’s NewConnect market for smaller companies.  Bank Pekao SA (PEO)   dropped for a second day, declining
1.6 zloty, or 1 percent, to 166.4 zloty as Poland’s second-
largest lender had its price estimate cut to 186 zloty from
195.3 zloty at Citigroup Inc.  To contact the reporter on this story:
